job.description:
&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Amun is a leading cryptocurrency issuer which aims to make purchasing crypto more&lt;br&gt;accessible, and efficient.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Under its 21Shares brand, Amun is the world&#39;s largest issuer of crypto exchange-traded&lt;br&gt;products (ETPs). The 21Shares suite of ETPs has simplified access to crypto for both&lt;br&gt;institutional and retail investors in the traditional finance community. In a similar fashion,&lt;br&gt;Amun aims to provide tokens that will make it easy for the crypto community to access&lt;br&gt;sophisticated strategies that are not otherwise readily available in this space. Amun 21Shares is a&lt;br&gt;team of entrepreneurs, engineers, and financial product developers who are uniquely&lt;br&gt;placed to revolutionize cryptocurrency investing through the issuance of our broad range&lt;br&gt;of tokens. Our goal is to make these tokens present a new paradigm in cryptocurrency&lt;br&gt;investing and to facilitate their use.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our investment in superior technology and automation has enabled us to both release&lt;br&gt;products, as well as work directly with top organizations including the Bitcoin Cash Foundation,&lt;br&gt;Bitcoin Suisse, Binance, Bitwise, Coinbase, FlowTraders, Sygnum, and the Tezos Foundation&lt;br&gt;as launch partners or customers of Onyx, our full stack issuance platform.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Amun 21Shares is looking to hire a Staff Accountant to join its rapidly growing finance team in its New York City office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review, prepare and post monthly journal entries including working with other teams to ensure completeness of accruals and proper revenue recognition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain Fixed Asset, Intangible and Prepaid schedules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reconcile monthly bank, credit card and cryptocurrency accounts/wallets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and analyze monthly and quarterly account reconciliations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform financial analyses, including balance sheet and income statement fluctuations analyses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Close general ledger monthly and prepare for internal and external reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the preparation of financial statements on an IFRS basis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the preparation of regulatory filings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with external auditors in year-end audit process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the design and implementation of proper internal controls to ensure a high degree of completeness and accuracy of the financial statements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ad-hoc assignments and special projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements / Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undergraduate degree in Accounting or related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in corporate accounting and/or audit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CPA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Asset management or general financial services experience, preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Public accounting experience, preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;IFRS experience, preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills, both quantitative and qualitative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intermediate to advanced MS Excel skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resourceful self-starter, with strong problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collegial and collaborative team player&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational skills; ability to handle a diverse workload in a deadline driven environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An interest in cryptocurrencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

